**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-6508 is to be kept in the original establishment where it was discovered. The building is to be locked down and closed to the public. Maintenance of SCP-6508 is to be performed 4 times a week. Assigned personnel must wear a protective suit to avoid direct contact with SCP-6508.

**Description:** SCP-6508 is a collection of 32 Mediterranean marine aquariums located in a specialized store in Huesca, Spain. All of the aquariums are populated by marine animals. Any mass of water within SCP-6508 will exhibit its anomalous effects. If a living human being comes into contact with this water mass, it will become an SCP-6508-1 instance.

SCP-6508-1 instances manifest physical traits from one of the animals that are present in SCP-6508. While the number of physical alterations is variable, all known SCP-6508-1 instances have retained the ability to breathe oxygen through the air.

